---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Digital Transformation for Ethiopian SMEs: Where to Start | Etacom Technology" description="Going digital doesn't have to be overwhelming. Here's where any Ethiopian business can start.">
  <Header homeLink="/" />

  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero-bg"></div>
      <div class="container page-hero-content">
        <a href="/blog" class="blog-back">&larr; Back to Blog</a>
        <span class="blog-category">Digital Transformation</span>
        <h1 class="page-hero-title">Digital Transformation for Ethiopian SMEs: Where to Start</h1>
        <p class="page-hero-desc">April 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container blog-content">
        <p>Going digital doesn't have to be overwhelming. For small and medium enterprises in Ethiopia, the journey starts with understanding where you are and what your biggest pain points are.</p>

        <h2>Step 1: Digitize Your Records</h2>
        <p>Many businesses still rely on paper-based systems. The first step is moving to digital — even if it's just Excel or Google Sheets. Track your inventory, sales, and expenses digitally. This alone can save hours of manual work each week.</p>

        <h2>Step 2: Automate Repetitive Tasks</h2>
        <p>Look for tasks that are repetitive and time-consuming: generating invoices, sending reminders, updating stock quantities. These can often be automated with simple software tools or custom-built solutions.</p>

        <h2>Step 3: Build an Online Presence</h2>
        <p>A website, a Google Business listing, or even a professional social media presence makes your business visible to customers who are searching online. In Ethiopia's growing digital economy, this is no longer optional.</p>

        <h2>Step 4: Invest in the Right Infrastructure</h2>
        <p>Reliable networking, servers, and security systems form the backbone of any digital operation. Without them, your software and data are at risk.</p>

        <h2>The Key Takeaway</h2>
        <p>Digital transformation is a journey, not a destination. Start small, measure results, and scale what works. You don't need a massive budget — you need a clear plan and the right partner.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero { position: relative; padding: 140px 0 80px; overflow: hidden; }
  .page-hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: var(--dark); }
  .page-hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-title { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 800; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .page-hero-desc { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
  .blog-back { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.875rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); text-decoration: none; margin-bottom: 16px; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .blog-back:hover { color: var(--white); }
  .blog-category { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: var(--primary); background: rgba(220,38,38,0.1); padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 50px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .blog-content { max-width: 720px; }
  .blog-content h2 { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--dark); margin: 32px 0 12px; }
  .blog-content p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 16px; }
</style>
